Peruâ€™s gold-export revenue dropped
17.2 percent in October from a year earlier on lower shipments,
the central bank said.  Gold sales of 429,900 ounces fell to $751 million from
544,300 ounces worth $907 million, the bank said in a statement
posted on its website today. Copper sales of 119,700 metric tons
rose 12.5 percent to $891 million, the bank said. Total metal
